Share fall in Asia
The Asian stock exchanges experienced a dramatic fall in shares on Tuesday, although some of the losses were finally cancelled during the day.
The Hong Kong Hang Seng stock exchange index described almost four percent in the course of trading, but later it deleted some of the losses and reduced the decrease to about 2.5 percent.
On the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, the Hang Seng China Enterprises Index, monitoring Chinese stocks, fell 3.8 percent, and the markets in Shanghai were closed.
The shares in the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but eventually the losses dropped to 4.3 percent.
