"The timing of the American rescue mission is uncertain and affects the world's financial markets," noted Joseph Yam, head of the Hong Kong Financial Council.
Hong Kong, although part of China, determines its financial policy independently, i.e. independently of the Chinese central bank.
In Hong Kong, interest rates are at the same level as in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, US legislators should start negotiations immediately and accept the financial system's proposal for support.
Otherwise, there is a threat that other countries will feel the consequences of this.
The Bloodbath of American Shares
On Monday, the U.S. House rejected the draft financial support, which should have spent $700 billion (almost 12 trillion kroner).
The legislators thus ignored President George Bush's call to support the plan.
According to Bush, the draft would solve the main causes of the financial crisis and help stabilise the economy as a whole.
On Monday, the US shares suffered a bloodbath and the leading stock indices recorded the biggest fall in 20 years.
Dow Jones fell by almost seven percent, with a similar rate of fall last year in 1987.
The index fell before the vote, but as soon as it turned out that the proposal was not adopted in the House, the index started to fall free.
Congress withdrew: The U.S. government will be able to pump $700 billion into banks
The chief leaders of the US Congress and the government of President George W. Bush have agreed on a broader form of agreement and financial assistance to the US financial system.
This will be voted on early next week.
The US legislators have made a breakthrough in the negotiations on the approval of the rescue plan in the form of financial assistance to the US financial system in the amount of 700 billion dollars (approximately 12 trillion kroner).
But there's no victory yet.
The convention must complete some details of the agreement before they can disclose the final form and vote of the law.
The draft financial support will be discussed in the House of Representatives on Monday.
That's what the Reuters news agency was briefed on Sunday by Barney Frank, Chairman of the Committee on Finance.
According to Senate sources, the draft may probably be voted on on Wednesday as soon as possible.
Economists believe that there should be an announcement that the rescue plan will be approved, which is the first important psychological factor in the revival of financial markets.
However, due to the complexity of the mechanisms, "well-being" will then take place.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We've taken a big step.
We have resolved our different views on what the form of the package for stabilising the market should be like," said the Bloomberg agency, the Democratic Nancy Pelosi.
He said the final vote could take place on Sunday.
The legislators met Henry Paulson, the US finance minister, on Saturday night to give the government a final form.
This should buy from financial companies the unselling mortgage assets that bring financial firms into serious losses and endanger the stability of the whole system.
"We are close to a final agreement on a draft that will work and which should also be effective on the market.
The plan for correction still needs to be continued, but I think we're there," said Paulson.
Signpost to Asian Trade
