The new law also limits the so-called "busy severance payments" of the directors participating in the programme and establishes a committee for monitoring the fund.
The fund should be run by the Treasury Department.
"We have worked very hard on this, and we have made great progress towards an agreement that will work and that will be useful to all Americans," Paulson said.
