According to statistics, 30-75% of motorists arrested for drunk driving are back in the car.
This would be prevented by Alcolock, since the system connected to the vehicle determines the alcohol level of the air sprayed into it. If it is higher than permitted or if the driver has not blown into the device at all, the system will not allow the car to start.
The cost of an instrument of more than 1000 euros would be a violation of the rules.
A study carried out in the 2007 US showed that vehicles equipped with such instruments could reduce the number of infringements by up to 65% in the first year after installation.
In Spain, it is estimated that this rule could save the lives of 115 people a year.
The measure focuses on offences for two reasons: it is easier to prevent them from turning into criminal offences,
on the other hand, it is easier to introduce because the legal reform is being implemented in the usual way, while the necessary reform of criminal matters requires a fundamental amendment.
The instrument is not yet available in any commercial form on the Spanish market, although it has already been installed in some industrial and public service vehicles in experimental mode.
The House will vote tomorrow on the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party to encourage the installation of the system in school buses, on a French model.
