At the same time, there are solutions such as reducing the level and duration of noise pollution that can significantly reduce these hearing losses.
The scientific opinion of the EU Scientific Committee states that for users of portable reproducing apparatus who listen to music at high volume (more than 89 decibels) for five hours a week, noise pollution exceeds the maximum currently in place for noise at work.
